WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.600 --> 00:00:06.540
I hope that one day I can do this
with my own children.

2
00:00:09.610 --> 00:00:11.870
Where did you get that?

3
00:00:11.950 --> 00:00:14.710
I went over to the snowman shop.

4
00:00:16.450 --> 00:00:18.110
An assassin!

5
00:00:18.190 --> 00:00:20.150
I'll protect you.
Your Majesty.

6
00:00:20.220 --> 00:00:23.380
I shall die for you!
You shall not take her!

7
00:00:23.460 --> 00:00:24.890
Find cover. my lady!

8
00:00:26.290 --> 00:00:28.230
- Nice arm.
- I'm getting some good ones.

9
00:00:28.300 --> 00:00:31.230
There's a boy.
That's a boy. Good try.

10
00:00:31.300 --> 00:00:33.290
- Got him.
- Help me.

11
00:01:30.520 --> 00:01:36.120
- What?
- I'm amazed. and I'm not easily amazed.

12
00:01:36.200 --> 00:01:38.790
- About what?
- How you can start a day...

13
00:01:38.870 --> 00:01:43.130
with one kind of expectation
and end up so completely different.

14
00:01:44.370 --> 00:01:47.640
Do you like the way
this day is turning out?

15
00:01:47.710 --> 00:01:50.300
I like It very much.

16
00:01:50.380 --> 00:01:53.970
It's a perfect day.
You couldn't plan a day like this.

17
00:01:54.050 --> 00:01:58.640
You can.
It just take an awful lot of work

18
00:01:58.720 --> 00:02:01.150
Come on in.
I want to show you something.

19
00:02:01.220 --> 00:02:03.660
- I don't think I should.
- I don't think you should either.

20
00:02:03.720 --> 00:02:07.660
That's why I'll show you one thing
and kick you out. Just one minute.

21
00:02:16.240 --> 00:02:18.500
It's just lovely.

22
00:02:28.920 --> 00:02:32.850
Would you like to sit and stare
at the fake fire?

23
00:02:36.420 --> 00:02:38.860
It's really a wonderful room.

24
00:02:38.930 --> 00:02:40.520
It is now.

25
00:02:47.600 --> 00:02:50.200
I don't know.
I don't think we should do this.

26
00:02:50.270 --> 00:02:51.700
I don't either.

27
00:02:54.610 --> 00:02:57.700
On second thought.
I think we should.

28
00:02:57.780 --> 00:03:00.870
It's the perfect end
to a perfect day.

29
00:03:01.950 --> 00:03:05.040
It's a little fast for me.

30
00:03:05.120 --> 00:03:06.880
Me too.

31
00:03:06.950 --> 00:03:09.220
Maybe I should go

32
00:03:09.290 --> 00:03:11.550
Where would you go?

33
00:03:11.630 --> 00:03:15.720
Why?.
We've got a perfect fire.

34
00:03:15.800 --> 00:03:18.560
I've got some French poetry here.
Baudelaire.

35
00:03:20.300 --> 00:03:21.890
I will read to you.

36
00:03:22.970 --> 00:03:25.060
I've got ice cream
on the windowsill.

37
00:03:25.140 --> 00:03:27.070
Hold on a minute.

38
00:03:32.480 --> 00:03:35.410
- Rocky Road?
- I love Rocky Road.

39
00:03:35.480 --> 00:03:37.750
I thought so

40
00:03:37.820 --> 00:03:39.410
You have to stay.

41
00:03:39.490 --> 00:03:43.750
I'm tired.
We can see each other tomorrow.

42
00:03:43.820 --> 00:03:47.590
Tonight.
It's gotta be tonight.

43
00:03:49.160 --> 00:03:52.600
- Really.
-Just stay for awhile.

44
00:03:52.670 --> 00:03:57.260
If you like it. stay for a while longer
and awhile longer.

45
00:03:57.340 --> 00:04:01.930
- Let's not spoil lt.
- I don't want to spoil It either.

46
00:04:02.010 --> 00:04:05.100
You know I can't stay with you.

47
00:04:05.180 --> 00:04:08.270
Why not? I love you.

48
00:04:10.350 --> 00:04:12.440
You love me?

49
00:04:12.520 --> 00:04:17.250
- You don't even know me.
- I know you.

50
00:04:19.190 --> 00:04:21.460
I can't believe I fell for this.

51
00:04:21.530 --> 00:04:24.120
This whole day has just been
one long setup.

52
00:04:24.200 --> 00:04:28.190
- It hasn't.
- And I hate fudge.

53
00:04:28.270 --> 00:04:30.530
No white chocolate.
No fudge.

54
00:04:30.600 --> 00:04:34.470
What are you doing?
Are you making some kind of list?

55
00:04:34.540 --> 00:04:38.140
Did you call my friends and ask
what I like and what I don't like?

56
00:04:38.210 --> 00:04:41.810
- Is this what love is for you?
- This is real. This is love.

57
00:04:41.880 --> 00:04:45.650
Stop saying that!
You must be crazy.

58
00:04:45.720 --> 00:04:49.490
I could never love someone like you.
You only love yourself.

59
00:04:49.560 --> 00:04:53.620
That's not true. I don't even like
myself. Give me another chance.

60
00:04:55.230 --> 00:04:57.490
That's for making me care about you.

61
00:05:04.370 --> 00:05:07.500
- I haven't done this since I was a kid.
- Me neither.

62
00:05:07.570 --> 00:05:10.340
- It's fun.
- Good. clean fun too.

63
00:05:10.410 --> 00:05:13.170
That's what's missing
in the world today.

64
00:05:13.250 --> 00:05:15.840
I can't wait to do this
with my own children.

65
00:05:15.920 --> 00:05:18.010
Golly. I want lots of kids!

66
00:05:18.090 --> 00:05:20.020
I want to adopt.
I want to have my own.

67
00:05:20.090 --> 00:05:23.680
I want foster kids.
I got this at Snowman City.

68
00:05:25.090 --> 00:05:27.580
Some kid threw
a snowball at us!

69
00:05:27.660 --> 00:05:30.600
Come here!
Let's have some fun!

70
00:05:33.430 --> 00:05:35.590
I wish these were my own kids!

71
00:05:38.770 --> 00:05:40.870
Are any of you up for adoption?

72
00:05:42.280 --> 00:05:44.770
Here's a humdinger over here!
Wasn't that great?

73
00:05:54.590 --> 00:05:56.350
Stop it!

74
00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:43.440
Over here!

75
00:06:45.510 --> 00:06:48.170
Where have you been?
You're missing all the fun.

76
00:06:48.240 --> 00:06:50.270
You look terrible.

77
00:06:50.340 --> 00:06:53.440
What happened?
Rough night?

78
00:07:11.800 --> 00:07:15.790
Okay. campers. rise and shine.

79
00:07:17.570 --> 00:07:20.800
Don't forget your booties
because It's cold out there today.

80
00:07:22.310 --> 00:07:25.040
It's cold out there every day.

81
00:07:25.110 --> 00:07:29.070
This country's largest lake. Chapala.
is located near the city....

82
00:07:29.150 --> 00:07:31.310
- of Guadalajara.
- What is Mexico?

83
00:07:32.650 --> 00:07:34.980
- Correct..
- "Lakes and Rivers. "400.

84
00:07:35.060 --> 00:07:38.390
Seneca is the largest of these lakes
in West-Central New York.

85
00:07:38.460 --> 00:07:40.950
- What are the Finger Lake?
- Correct..

86
00:07:41.030 --> 00:07:42.960
- That's amazing.
- "Lakes and Rivers" for 600.

87
00:07:43.030 --> 00:07:45.590
This South American lake drains
into the smaller lake in Bolivia.

88
00:07:45.670 --> 00:07:49.400
- What is Titicaca?
- Correct..

89
00:07:49.470 --> 00:07:51.840
- "Lakes and Rivers" for 1.000.
- Milky colored...

90
00:07:51.910 --> 00:07:53.340
- from glacial clay...
- What is the rhone?

91
00:07:53.410 --> 00:07:57.340
when entering. Lake Geneva.
this river is clear upon exiting..

92
00:07:57.410 --> 00:08:00.180
Jim?
The Rhone is good for $1.000.

93
00:08:00.250 --> 00:08:05.080
- You are $500 off the lead.
- Let's go to "Inventors" for 200.

94
00:08:05.150 --> 00:08:07.450
This is pitiful.

95
00:08:07.520 --> 00:08:12.250
A thousand people freezing their butts
off. waiting to worship a rat.

96
00:08:12.330 --> 00:08:15.990
What a hype. Groundhog Day used
to mean something in this town.

97
00:08:16.060 --> 00:08:18.690
They used to pull the hog out
and eat it!

98
00:08:18.770 --> 00:08:21.860
You're hypocrites. all of you!

99
00:08:24.100 --> 00:08:27.340
You got a problem
with what I'm saying?

100
00:08:27.410 --> 00:08:30.170
Until your tongue.
and you come out here and talk.

101
00:08:30.240 --> 00:08:32.210
Am I upsetting you. Princess?

102
00:08:32.280 --> 00:08:37.310
You want a prediction about the weather.
you're asking the wrong Phil.

103
00:08:37.380 --> 00:08:40.290
I'll give you a winter prediction.

104
00:08:40.350 --> 00:08:42.650
It's gonna be cold...

105
00:08:42.720 --> 00:08:44.880
It's gonna be gray...

106
00:08:44.960 --> 00:08:50.120
and It's gonna last you
for the rest of your life.

107
00:09:24.330 --> 00:09:28.770
Once again. the eyes of the nation
have turned here to this...

108
00:09:28.840 --> 00:09:31.100
tiny village
in western Pennsylvania.

109
00:09:32.440 --> 00:09:35.430
There is no way that
this winter...

110
00:09:35.510 --> 00:09:38.540
Is ever going to end...

111
00:09:38.610 --> 00:09:42.570
as long as this groundhog
keeps seeing his shadow.

112
00:09:42.650 --> 00:09:44.670
I don't see any other way out.

113
00:09:45.550 --> 00:09:47.490
He has to be stopped.

114
00:09:48.690 --> 00:09:50.250
I have to stop him.

115
00:09:52.760 --> 00:09:54.590
Real good. Phil.

116
00:09:56.700 --> 00:09:58.290
He's crazy.

117
00:10:02.940 --> 00:10:06.200
I'm worried. I think there's something
really wrong with Phil.

118
00:10:06.270 --> 00:10:08.900
There's a lot of things
really wrong with Phil.

119
00:10:13.080 --> 00:10:15.380
I've come to the end of me.

120
00:10:15.450 --> 00:10:18.820
There's no way out now.

121
00:10:18.890 --> 00:10:22.320
I just want you to remember
we had a beautiful day together once.

122
00:10:25.660 --> 00:10:29.190
All right. little fella.
Good job.

123
00:10:29.260 --> 00:10:31.890
- He smiled at me. Did you see that?
- I believe he did.

124
00:10:33.530 --> 00:10:35.690
Okay. little fella.
There you go

125
00:10:38.240 --> 00:10:40.670
Hl. mister.
Something I can do you for?.

126
00:10:43.310 --> 00:10:45.240
What are you doing?

127
00:10:49.950 --> 00:10:52.080
Jake. get the word out!
Somebody kidnapped Phil!

128
00:10:52.150 --> 00:10:53.740
We're going after him!

129
00:11:00.230 --> 00:11:03.250
Why would anybody steal a groundhog?

130
00:11:03.330 --> 00:11:06.320
I can probably think
of a couple of reasons. Pervert.

131
00:11:32.130 --> 00:11:35.690
- He must have just snapped!
- This should be good.

132
00:11:38.130 --> 00:11:41.070
What is he doing?
What can he be thinking?

133
00:11:41.130 --> 00:11:43.570
That's not bad
for a quadruped.

134
00:11:43.640 --> 00:11:47.470
You gotta check your mirrors.
Just the side of your eye.

135
00:11:53.410 --> 00:11:55.140
That's lt.

136
00:11:55.220 --> 00:11:57.840
They're chasing us!
Come on. make It fun!

137
00:12:06.330 --> 00:12:09.120
Don't drive angry.

138
00:12:29.120 --> 00:12:33.750
Hot dog! There's no way out except
the way we came in. We got him now!

139
00:12:52.710 --> 00:12:55.500
- What is he doing?
- I don't know.

140
00:12:59.610 --> 00:13:02.640
If you gotta shoot. aim high.
I don't wanna hit the groundhog.

141
00:13:06.990 --> 00:13:09.180
We mustn't keep
our public waiting.

142
00:13:12.390 --> 00:13:13.860
It's show time.

143
00:13:20.130 --> 00:13:22.570
All right. on me. Larry.
in three!

144
00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:27.560
Two. one.

145
00:13:44.420 --> 00:13:45.890
He might be okay.

146
00:13:50.600 --> 00:13:53.090
Probably not now.

147
00:14:08.820 --> 00:14:10.840
Nuts.

148
00:14:17.890 --> 00:14:21.220
Did you sleep well. Mr. Connors?

149
00:14:21.290 --> 00:14:24.920
Would you like some toast?

150
00:14:42.820 --> 00:14:46.380
- What's going on?
- My God.

151
00:15:18.650 --> 00:15:20.080
That's him.

152
00:15:23.090 --> 00:15:26.750
He was a really great guy.

153
00:15:26.830 --> 00:15:29.660
I really liked him a lot.

154
00:15:37.140 --> 00:15:37.270
I'm sorry.
What was that again?

155
00:15:37.270 --> 00:15:39.360
I'm sorry.
What was that again?

156
00:15:39.440 --> 00:15:42.530
- I'm a god!
- You're a god?

157
00:15:42.610 --> 00:15:45.980
I'm a god.
I'm not the God. I don't think.

158
00:15:46.050 --> 00:15:48.640
Because you survived a car wreck?

159
00:15:48.720 --> 00:15:50.310
You ready to order?.

160
00:15:50.380 --> 00:15:53.550
I didn't just survive a wreck.
I wasn't just blown up yesterday.

161
00:15:53.620 --> 00:15:56.490
I have been stabbed.
shot poisoned...

162
00:15:56.560 --> 00:15:59.490
frozen. hung. electrocuted...

163
00:15:59.560 --> 00:16:01.820
- and burned.
- Really?.

164
00:16:01.900 --> 00:16:06.660
Every morning I wake up fine.
not a dent in the fender.

165
00:16:06.730 --> 00:16:10.670
- I am an immortal.
- Special today is blueberry waffles.

166
00:16:10.740 --> 00:16:12.730
Why are you telling me this?

167
00:16:12.810 --> 00:16:15.140
Because I want you
to believe in me.

168
00:16:15.210 --> 00:16:20.310
You're not a god. Believe me. This is
12 years of Catholic school talking.

169
00:16:20.380 --> 00:16:22.810
I could come back
if you're not ready.

170
00:16:22.880 --> 00:16:25.180
How do you know I'm not a god?

171
00:16:25.250 --> 00:16:29.090
Please!
Because It's not possible!

172
00:16:29.160 --> 00:16:32.220
- I'll come back.
- Doris!

173
00:16:36.100 --> 00:16:38.860
This is Doris. Her brother-in-law.
Carl. owns this diner.

174
00:16:38.930 --> 00:16:43.490
She's worked here since she was 1 7.
She wants to see Paris before she dies.

175
00:16:43.570 --> 00:16:45.970
- Boy. would l!
- What are you doing?

176
00:16:46.040 --> 00:16:49.600
- Debbie Klelser and her fiance. Fred.
- Do I know you?

177
00:16:49.680 --> 00:16:52.800
They're supposed to be married this
afternoon. but Debbie is reconsidering.

178
00:16:52.880 --> 00:16:55.850
- What?
- Lovely ring.

179
00:16:55.920 --> 00:16:58.110
This is Bill who's been a walter
for three years...

180
00:16:58.180 --> 00:17:00.680
since he left Penn State
and had to get work

181
00:17:00.750 --> 00:17:03.590
He like the town. paints toy soldiers.
and he's gay.

182
00:17:03.660 --> 00:17:05.520
I am.

183
00:17:05.590 --> 00:17:08.690
This is Gus. He hates his life here
and wishes he'd stayed in the Navy.

184
00:17:08.760 --> 00:17:11.420
I could have retired on half pay
after 20 years.

185
00:17:11.500 --> 00:17:13.560
Is this some kind of trick?

186
00:17:13.630 --> 00:17:16.530
Maybe the real God uses tricks.
Maybe He's not omnipotent.

187
00:17:16.600 --> 00:17:19.730
He's just been around so long.
He knows everything.

188
00:17:19.810 --> 00:17:21.240
- Who's that?
- This is Tom.

189
00:17:21.310 --> 00:17:23.540
He worked in the coal mine
till they closed It down.

190
00:17:23.610 --> 00:17:25.040
- Her?.
- Alice.

191
00:17:25.110 --> 00:17:27.740
She came from Ireland as a baby
and lived in Erie most of her life.

192
00:17:27.810 --> 00:17:29.940
- He's right.
- Nancy.

193
00:17:30.020 --> 00:17:34.750
She works in the dress shop and make
chipmunk noises when she gets excited.

194
00:17:34.820 --> 00:17:36.760
- It's true.
- How do you know these people?

195
00:17:36.820 --> 00:17:41.620
I know everything. I n five seconds.
a walter will drop a tray of dishes.

196
00:17:41.690 --> 00:17:44.490
- Five. four. three. two. one.
- This is nuts.

197
00:17:47.270 --> 00:17:48.700
That's enough.

198
00:17:50.340 --> 00:17:54.140
- Do you know me too?
- I know all about you.

199
00:17:54.210 --> 00:17:57.010
You like producing. but you're hoping
for more than Channel 9 Pittsburgh.

200
00:17:57.080 --> 00:17:59.600
Everyone knows that.

201
00:17:59.680 --> 00:18:02.940
You like boats. but not the ocean.

202
00:18:03.020 --> 00:18:06.580
You go to a mountain lake in the summer
with your family.

203
00:18:06.650 --> 00:18:08.680
There's a long. wooden dock
and a boathouse...

204
00:18:08.760 --> 00:18:10.780
with boards missing
from the roof....

205
00:18:10.860 --> 00:18:14.190
and a place you used to crawl
underneath to be alone.

206
00:18:14.260 --> 00:18:18.630
You're a sucker for French poetry
and rhinestones.

207
00:18:18.700 --> 00:18:20.460
You're very generous.

208
00:18:20.530 --> 00:18:23.400
You're kind to strangers
and children.

209
00:18:23.470 --> 00:18:26.300
And when you stand in the snow.
you look like an angel.

210
00:18:26.370 --> 00:18:28.310
How are you doing this?

211
00:18:29.440 --> 00:18:34.310
I wake up every day right here...

212
00:18:34.380 --> 00:18:37.870
In Punxsutawney.
and It's always February 2.

213
00:18:38.950 --> 00:18:41.390
There's nothing
I can do about lt.

214
00:18:42.220 --> 00:18:45.380
If you still doubt me...

215
00:18:45.460 --> 00:18:47.930
In ten seconds...

216
00:18:47.990 --> 00:18:51.690
Larry will come through that door
and take you away from me...

217
00:18:51.760 --> 00:18:54.490
but you can't let him.

218
00:18:54.570 --> 00:18:57.540
Please believe me.
You've got to believe me.

219
00:19:02.710 --> 00:19:06.640
You ready?. We better get going if we're
going to stay ahead of the weather.

220
00:19:06.710 --> 00:19:08.980
What's that?

221
00:19:17.490 --> 00:19:19.420
Maybe It really is happening.

222
00:19:19.490 --> 00:19:21.590
How else could you know so much?

223
00:19:21.660 --> 00:19:24.150
There is no way.
I'm not that smart.

224
00:19:25.330 --> 00:19:27.770
Maybe I should spend the day
with you...

225
00:19:27.830 --> 00:19:31.360
as an objective witness.
Just to see what happens.

226
00:19:31.440 --> 00:19:34.170
This sounds
like a science project.

227
00:19:35.140 --> 00:19:37.840
Concentrate.
You gotta want lt.

228
00:19:41.510 --> 00:19:45.210
It's more in the wrist than the finger.
It's just gotta-

229
00:19:53.530 --> 00:19:55.460
Be the hat! Come on! Go!

230
00:19:55.530 --> 00:19:57.460
It would take me a year
to get good at this.

231
00:19:57.530 --> 00:20:02.060
Six months. Four to five hours a day.
and you'd be an expert.

232
00:20:02.140 --> 00:20:04.500
Is this what you do
with eternity?.

233
00:20:04.570 --> 00:20:06.200
Now you know.

234
00:20:07.610 --> 00:20:09.600
That's not the worst part.

235
00:20:09.680 --> 00:20:11.610
What's the worst part?

236
00:20:11.680 --> 00:20:16.480
The worst part is that tomorrow you
will have forgotten all about this...

237
00:20:16.550 --> 00:20:19.750
and you'll treat me
like a jerk again.

238
00:20:19.820 --> 00:20:23.410
- It's all right. I am a jerk
- You're not.

239
00:20:23.490 --> 00:20:25.550
It doesn't make any difference.

240
00:20:25.630 --> 00:20:30.260
I've killed myself so many times.
I don't even exist anymore.

241
00:20:30.330 --> 00:20:33.660
Sometimes I wish
I had a thousand lifetimes.

242
00:20:33.730 --> 00:20:37.360
I don't know. Phil.
Maybe It's not a curse.

243
00:20:37.440 --> 00:20:39.960
It just depends on
how you look at lt.

244
00:20:41.740 --> 00:20:43.940
Gosh. you're an upbeat lady!

245
00:20:47.180 --> 00:20:51.670
- It's been a really nice day for me.
- Me too.

246
00:20:51.750 --> 00:20:56.780
Maybe. if it's not too boring.
we could do It again sometime.

247
00:20:56.860 --> 00:20:58.790
I hope so

248
00:21:10.740 --> 00:21:12.290
You're still here.

249
00:21:13.910 --> 00:21:17.840
I thought you were supposed
to disappear or I was or something!

250
00:21:17.910 --> 00:21:20.400
Not until 6:00.

251
00:21:20.480 --> 00:21:22.110
You rat!

252
00:21:22.180 --> 00:21:23.910
I never said midnight.

253
00:21:23.980 --> 00:21:28.940
- You knew I was waiting for midnight!
- Does this mean you're gonna leave?

254
00:21:32.430 --> 00:21:33.860
Good.

255
00:21:44.570 --> 00:21:46.000
I'm sorry.

256
00:21:47.770 --> 00:21:50.940
It's all right.
You can fall asleep.

257
00:21:51.010 --> 00:21:55.340
I promise
I won't touch you. much.

258
00:21:56.620 --> 00:22:00.020
That's all right.
I'm not tired.

259
00:22:00.090 --> 00:22:02.110
What were you saying?

260
00:22:03.320 --> 00:22:06.690
I think the last thing
that you heard was...

261
00:22:06.760 --> 00:22:09.280
"Only God can make a tree."

262
00:22:09.360 --> 00:22:10.800
Really?.

263
00:22:49.070 --> 00:22:51.000
What I wanted to say was...

264
00:22:53.040 --> 00:22:58.410
I think you're the kindest. sweetest.
prettiest person...

265
00:22:58.480 --> 00:23:00.570
I've ever met in my life.

266
00:23:02.050 --> 00:23:04.780
I've never seen anyone...

267
00:23:04.850 --> 00:23:07.250
that's nicer to people
than you are.

268
00:23:20.500 --> 00:23:23.370
The first time I saw you...

269
00:23:23.440 --> 00:23:26.930
something happened to me.

270
00:23:27.010 --> 00:23:29.440
I never told you. but...

271
00:23:32.580 --> 00:23:37.110
I knew that I wanted
to hold you as hard as I could.

272
00:23:49.960 --> 00:23:53.130
I don't deserve someone like you.

273
00:23:56.240 --> 00:23:59.530
But if I ever could...

274
00:23:59.610 --> 00:24:01.940
I swear I would love you...

275
00:24:02.010 --> 00:24:04.130
for the rest of my life.

276
00:24:08.750 --> 00:24:10.810
Did you say something?

277
00:24:16.320 --> 00:24:17.760
Good night.

278
00:25:30.330 --> 00:25:32.760
Who wants coffee?
Get It while It's hot.

279
00:25:32.830 --> 00:25:34.600
Thanks. Phil.

280
00:25:34.670 --> 00:25:39.700
- Larry?. Skim milk. two sugars.
- Thanks. Phil.

281
00:25:39.770 --> 00:25:42.330
- Pastry?.
- We're just setting up.

282
00:25:42.410 --> 00:25:44.310
Take your pick.

283
00:25:45.580 --> 00:25:47.640
Thanks. Raspberry. Great.

284
00:25:47.710 --> 00:25:51.240
I was just talking with Buster Green.
the head groundhog honcho

285
00:25:51.320 --> 00:25:54.310
He said if we set up over here.
we might get a better shot.

286
00:25:54.390 --> 00:25:57.050
- What do you think?
- Sounds good.

287
00:25:57.120 --> 00:25:58.590
What do you think?

288
00:25:59.890 --> 00:26:01.830
Let's go for lt.

289
00:26:01.890 --> 00:26:04.890
- Good work
- Maybe we'll get lucky .

290
00:26:04.960 --> 00:26:06.900
Let me help you
with the heavy stuff..

291
00:26:08.670 --> 00:26:11.600
You got your coffee.
I'll get lt.

292
00:26:12.710 --> 00:26:14.640
We never talk.
Do you have kids?

293
00:26:49.340 --> 00:26:51.280
I'd like a piano lesson. please.

294
00:26:51.340 --> 00:26:55.780
I'm with a student now. If you come
back tomorrow. I can squeeze you in.

295
00:26:55.850 --> 00:26:59.010
I kind of want to get started.
I could give you $1 .000.

296
00:27:01.250 --> 00:27:02.690
Come on in.

297
00:27:22.410 --> 00:27:24.500
Good morning!
Off to see the groundhog?

298
00:27:27.650 --> 00:27:30.170
You think It will be
an early spring?

299
00:27:30.250 --> 00:27:32.770
"Winter slumbering in the open air...

300
00:27:32.850 --> 00:27:34.790
wears on his smiling face...

301
00:27:34.850 --> 00:27:36.820
a dream of spring."

302
00:28:18.900 --> 00:28:20.330
How's she look?

303
00:28:20.400 --> 00:28:22.960
- Great.
- Thank you.

304
00:28:23.040 --> 00:28:25.000
Did you know
he could ice sculpt?

305
00:28:40.790 --> 00:28:43.880
Not bad.
You say this is your first lesson?

306
00:28:44.820 --> 00:28:47.550
My father was a piano mover.

307
00:28:54.100 --> 00:28:56.260
I thought It was you.

308
00:29:00.170 --> 00:29:02.800
I have missed you so much.

309
00:29:06.780 --> 00:29:10.720
I don't know where you're headed.
but can you call in sick?

310
00:29:14.120 --> 00:29:16.820
I gotta get going.

311
00:29:16.890 --> 00:29:18.950
It's good to see you.

312
00:29:37.040 --> 00:29:39.200
Hello. father.

313
00:29:39.280 --> 00:29:42.770
Let's get you someplace warm.

314
00:29:42.850 --> 00:29:44.280
Remember me?

315
00:29:49.420 --> 00:29:52.480
Excuse me. sir. Are you the one
who brought the old man in?

316
00:29:52.560 --> 00:29:54.550
How is he?

317
00:29:54.630 --> 00:29:56.990
He just passed away.

318
00:29:58.230 --> 00:30:00.160
What did he die of?.

319
00:30:00.230 --> 00:30:03.500
He was just old.
It was just his time.

320
00:30:06.310 --> 00:30:09.370
- I want to see his chart. Excuse me.
- Sir!

321
00:30:09.440 --> 00:30:11.600
You can't come in here.

322
00:30:11.680 --> 00:30:14.340
This is a restricted area.

323
00:30:23.360 --> 00:30:25.590
Where's the chart?

324
00:30:25.660 --> 00:30:28.850
Sometimes people just die.

325
00:30:28.930 --> 00:30:30.860
Not today.

326
00:30:42.710 --> 00:30:44.640
It's hard down there
at the bottom.

327
00:30:47.880 --> 00:30:50.540
- Here you go
- Thank you.

328
00:30:54.890 --> 00:30:56.880
Come on. Dad!
Come on. Pop!

329
00:31:00.930 --> 00:31:03.550
Breathe. Pop!

330
00:31:30.090 --> 00:31:32.680
When Chekhov
saw the long winter...

331
00:31:32.760 --> 00:31:36.660
he saw a winter bleak and dark
and bereft of hope.

332
00:31:36.730 --> 00:31:41.670
Yet we know that winter is just
another step in the cycle of life.

333
00:31:41.730 --> 00:31:45.600
But standing here
among the people of Punxsutawney...

334
00:31:45.670 --> 00:31:48.400
and basking in the warmth
of their hearths and hearts...

335
00:31:49.510 --> 00:31:51.770
I couldn't imagine a better fate...

336
00:31:51.840 --> 00:31:55.110
than a long and lustrous winter.

337
00:31:55.180 --> 00:31:58.170
From Punxsutawney.
It's Phil Connors.

338
00:31:58.250 --> 00:31:59.680
So long.

339
00:32:01.390 --> 00:32:03.320
Very nice speech. Phil.

340
00:32:03.390 --> 00:32:05.720
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

341
00:32:05.790 --> 00:32:09.020
- How was that for you two?
- Man. you touched me.

342
00:32:09.090 --> 00:32:11.030
- Thanks. Larry.
- Thank you.

343
00:32:12.560 --> 00:32:14.830
I gotta go

344
00:32:14.900 --> 00:32:19.100
That was surprising.
I didn't know you were so versatile.

345
00:32:19.170 --> 00:32:21.110
I surprise myself sometimes.

346
00:32:21.170 --> 00:32:23.230
Would you like
to get some coffee?

347
00:32:23.310 --> 00:32:27.300
I'd love to. Can I have a rain check?
I've got some errands to run.

348
00:32:30.980 --> 00:32:34.920
What errands?
I thought we were going back.

349
00:32:44.600 --> 00:32:46.360
Hold it. fella!

350
00:32:53.170 --> 00:32:56.000
What do you say?.

351
00:32:56.070 --> 00:32:59.510
You little brat.
You have never thanked me!

352
00:32:59.580 --> 00:33:02.840
I'll see you tomorrow. maybe!

353
00:33:09.960 --> 00:33:12.690
- Now what?
- You've totaled lt.

354
00:33:12.760 --> 00:33:17.860
It's only a flat tire.
Now just be patient. Just cool it!

355
00:33:17.930 --> 00:33:21.830
- It's an earthquake!
- It's not an earthquake!

356
00:33:21.900 --> 00:33:23.330
What is it?

357
00:33:26.610 --> 00:33:28.700
Thank you. young man.

358
00:33:29.840 --> 00:33:32.330
It's nothing.
I had the tire and the jack.

359
00:33:32.410 --> 00:33:35.110
Just be comfortable.
Be a minute.

360
00:33:35.180 --> 00:33:36.700
Who is that?

361
00:33:36.780 --> 00:33:39.550
Must be from the motor club.

362
00:33:41.050 --> 00:33:43.750
- My God! He's having a heart attack!
- What should I do?

363
00:33:43.820 --> 00:33:47.220
- Call an ambulance. a lawyer. a doctor!
- Mom. I don't think he's breathing!

364
00:33:55.170 --> 00:33:57.100
I think that did lt.

365
00:34:00.540 --> 00:34:03.470
If you're gonna eat steak.
get some sharper teeth.

366
00:34:03.540 --> 00:34:06.240
- Enjoy your lunch.
- Thank you.

367
00:34:06.310 --> 00:34:09.040
Who was that? I'm fine.

368
00:34:09.110 --> 00:34:11.910
- Are you sure?
- Oh. yes. Eat.

369
00:34:16.320 --> 00:34:18.980
People just don't understand
what is involved in this.

370
00:34:19.060 --> 00:34:20.990
This is an art form.

371
00:34:21.060 --> 00:34:23.790
You know. I think most people
Just think that...

372
00:34:23.860 --> 00:34:27.030
I hold the camera
and point It at stuff..

373
00:34:27.100 --> 00:34:29.570
There is a lot more to It
than just that.

374
00:34:31.470 --> 00:34:34.770
Would you be at all interested
in seeing the inside of the van?

375
00:34:34.840 --> 00:34:38.740
You know. I really have to get back
to the party.

376
00:34:38.810 --> 00:34:42.770
Great idea. I'll go with you.
Let me just drop a tip here.

377
00:34:49.890 --> 00:34:52.760
How are you?
Rita. this is Nancy.

378
00:34:52.820 --> 00:34:55.260
We were just going
to the party.

379
00:34:55.330 --> 00:34:57.260
- You going?
- Sounds like fun.

380
00:34:57.330 --> 00:34:59.920
Maybe we should call Phil.

381
00:35:00.000 --> 00:35:02.060
- I think he's already in there.
- Great.

382
00:36:58.750 --> 00:37:01.580
- Isn't he good?
- He's great!

383
00:37:01.650 --> 00:37:03.590
He's my student.

384
00:37:05.890 --> 00:37:07.830
I'm so proud.

385
00:37:08.960 --> 00:37:10.390
Thank you.

386
00:37:11.360 --> 00:37:13.460
Welcome to our party.

387
00:37:13.530 --> 00:37:17.300
-I didn't know you could play like that.
-I'm versatile.

388
00:37:25.240 --> 00:37:28.270
It's that nice. young man
from the motor club.

389
00:37:28.350 --> 00:37:31.650
- Thank you again.
- It's nothing. ladles.

390
00:37:31.720 --> 00:37:35.120
He's the fastest jack
in Jefferson County.

391
00:37:37.490 --> 00:37:39.420
What was that all about?

392
00:37:39.490 --> 00:37:42.520
I really don't know.
They've been hitting on me all night.

393
00:37:43.400 --> 00:37:44.830
There you are.

394
00:37:46.700 --> 00:37:50.100
I never thanked you properly
for what you did for Buster.

395
00:37:50.170 --> 00:37:52.530
He would have choked for sure.

396
00:37:52.600 --> 00:37:56.440
He may have.
He was trying to swallow a whole cow.

397
00:37:56.510 --> 00:38:00.600
- I owe you one. buddy.
- Hang onto him. dear. He's a real find.

398
00:38:03.480 --> 00:38:07.010
- What did you do today?.
- Same old. same old.

399
00:38:12.660 --> 00:38:14.390
Excuse me.

400
00:38:14.460 --> 00:38:16.390
Fred. how was the wedding?

401
00:38:16.460 --> 00:38:19.660
I just wanted to thank you
for making Debbie go through with lt.

402
00:38:19.730 --> 00:38:22.890
All I did was fan the flame
of her passion for you.

403
00:38:22.970 --> 00:38:25.560
You are the best.

404
00:38:25.640 --> 00:38:28.870
Rita.
this is Debbie and Fred Klelser.

405
00:38:28.940 --> 00:38:32.210
- Here you go. kids. Congratulations.
- What is this?

406
00:38:32.280 --> 00:38:35.410
No way!

407
00:38:35.480 --> 00:38:36.910
Wrestlemania!

408
00:38:39.520 --> 00:38:42.580
How did you know?
We're gonna be in Pittsburgh anyway!

409
00:38:42.650 --> 00:38:46.520
- Thank you! You're a real pal!
- This is the best!

410
00:38:51.530 --> 00:38:55.300
- I don't understand.
- I guess not.

411
00:38:55.370 --> 00:38:57.840
How does everyone know you?
You only come here once a year.

412
00:38:57.900 --> 00:39:00.460
You seem like the most popular person
in town.

413
00:39:00.540 --> 00:39:02.870
Excuse me. Dr. Connors?

414
00:39:02.940 --> 00:39:05.740
I want to thank you
for fixing Felix's back.

415
00:39:05.810 --> 00:39:08.180
He can even help
around the house again.

416
00:39:08.250 --> 00:39:10.710
I'm sorry to hear that. Felix.

417
00:39:13.220 --> 00:39:15.150
"Dr. Connors"?

418
00:39:15.220 --> 00:39:17.780
It's kind of an honorary title.

419
00:39:17.860 --> 00:39:20.650
- What is going on?
- I really don't know.

420
00:39:20.730 --> 00:39:23.960
There is something
going on with you.

421
00:39:24.030 --> 00:39:26.120
Would you like the long version
or the short one?

422
00:39:26.200 --> 00:39:28.960
Let's start with the short
and go from there.

423
00:39:34.710 --> 00:39:37.470
Okay. folks. Attention.

424
00:39:37.540 --> 00:39:40.880
Time for the big bachelor auction.
You all know the rules.

425
00:39:40.950 --> 00:39:43.410
All the eligible bachelors
come down in front...

426
00:39:43.480 --> 00:39:46.750
and you ladles bid on them!

427
00:39:46.820 --> 00:39:50.880
You get to do whatever you want
with them. No questions asked!

428
00:39:50.960 --> 00:39:54.220
I don't want to know about it.
as long as It's legal!

429
00:39:54.290 --> 00:39:58.090
Get out your pocketbooks and remember.
It's all for charity!

430
00:40:01.030 --> 00:40:04.330
What are you doing down here?
Go on. Get up there.

431
00:40:04.400 --> 00:40:07.890
I got ten bucks that
says you're mine!

432
00:40:07.970 --> 00:40:11.460
- Buster. I got your first victim.
- Come up here!

433
00:40:17.850 --> 00:40:21.220
All right! What am I bid
for this fine specimen?

434
00:40:21.290 --> 00:40:22.910
Five dollars!

435
00:40:22.990 --> 00:40:25.080
The bidding has begun
at five dollars.

436
00:40:25.160 --> 00:40:28.060
- Ten dollars!
- Fifteen!

437
00:40:28.130 --> 00:40:30.250
- Twenty!
- Twenty-five!

438
00:40:30.330 --> 00:40:32.520
- Thirty!
- Thirty-five!

439
00:40:32.600 --> 00:40:34.620
- Forty!
- Forty-five!

440
00:40:34.700 --> 00:40:37.570
- Fifty!
- Fifty-five!

441
00:40:37.640 --> 00:40:40.630
- Sixty!
- I'm bid sixty. Do I hear more?

442
00:40:44.510 --> 00:40:47.710
Three hundred and thirty-nine dollars
and eighty-eight cents!

443
00:40:52.480 --> 00:40:55.540
We can't accept any more bids.
That's sold...

444
00:40:55.620 --> 00:40:59.280
to the little lady for $339.88!

445
00:41:00.360 --> 00:41:01.790
Congratulations.

446
00:41:09.870 --> 00:41:11.800
Okay. bachelors!
Who's next?

447
00:41:21.850 --> 00:41:25.510
All right!
What am I bid for this guy?.

448
00:41:25.580 --> 00:41:27.570
Do I hear a buck and a half?.

449
00:41:27.650 --> 00:41:29.920
Anybody?.

450
00:41:29.990 --> 00:41:33.010
- Seventy-five cents?
- I bid two bits!

451
00:41:33.090 --> 00:41:36.030
Sold to the lady
for twenty-five cents!

452
00:41:36.090 --> 00:41:37.720
I got him!

453
00:41:46.100 --> 00:41:48.800
Phil Connors!
I thought that was you!

454
00:41:48.870 --> 00:41:51.600
This is Ned Ryerson.
my new insurance agent.

455
00:41:51.680 --> 00:41:53.110
I'll say!

456
00:41:54.180 --> 00:41:56.270
I have not seen this guy
for 20 years.

457
00:41:56.350 --> 00:41:59.320
He comes to me and buys whole life.
term. uniflex...

458
00:41:59.380 --> 00:42:01.410
fire. theft. auto.
dental. health...

459
00:42:01.490 --> 00:42:04.680
with the optional death
and dismemberment plan. water damage.

460
00:42:04.760 --> 00:42:07.160
This is the best day of my life.

461
00:42:07.230 --> 00:42:09.420
Mine too.

462
00:42:09.490 --> 00:42:12.730
- Where are we going?
- Let's not spoil lt.

463
00:42:15.630 --> 00:42:17.070
I got that!

464
00:42:20.070 --> 00:42:23.560
- Why can't I look?
- Because you bother me a lot.

465
00:42:23.640 --> 00:42:27.100
I'm getting cold.
How much longer do I have to sit here?

466
00:42:27.180 --> 00:42:30.840
I'm just giving you your money's worth.
You paid top dollar for me.

467
00:42:30.920 --> 00:42:33.750
I think you were a bargain.

468
00:42:33.820 --> 00:42:36.720
Sweet of you to say.
You're probably right.

469
00:42:39.520 --> 00:42:42.150
- Is It finished yet?
- Almost.

470
00:42:42.230 --> 00:42:46.060
I still have to put cherry syrup on top
and then we can eat lt.

471
00:42:46.130 --> 00:42:48.830
Come on!
I'm freezing!

472
00:42:48.900 --> 00:42:51.770
One second. All right.
Let me turn toward the light.

473
00:42:58.280 --> 00:42:59.740
It's amazing.

474
00:43:00.450 --> 00:43:02.380
It's beautiful.

475
00:43:06.020 --> 00:43:09.890
- How did you do that?
- I know your face so well...

476
00:43:09.950 --> 00:43:12.010
I could have done It
with my eyes closed.

477
00:43:16.660 --> 00:43:20.600
It's lovely.
I don't know what to say.

478
00:43:21.830 --> 00:43:23.270
I do

479
00:43:25.040 --> 00:43:27.530
No matter what happens tomorrow...

480
00:43:27.610 --> 00:43:29.630
or for the rest of my life...

481
00:43:29.710 --> 00:43:33.470
I'm happy now
because I love you.

482
00:43:35.180 --> 00:43:37.110
I think I'm happy too.

483
00:44:35.640 --> 00:44:38.230
- Please. not again.
- That is a great song!

484
00:44:38.310 --> 00:44:39.940
- It's not!
- Don't listen to this man-

485
00:44:42.110 --> 00:44:44.450
It's too early.

486
00:44:54.960 --> 00:44:57.330
Something is different.

487
00:44:57.400 --> 00:44:58.860
Good or bad?

488
00:44:58.930 --> 00:45:01.420
Anything different is good...

489
00:45:03.700 --> 00:45:05.860
but this could be real good.

490
00:45:10.780 --> 00:45:12.710
Why are you here?

491
00:45:12.780 --> 00:45:15.180
I bought you. I own you.

492
00:45:17.220 --> 00:45:19.150
But why are you still here?

493
00:45:19.220 --> 00:45:21.910
You said stay. so I stayed.

494
00:45:24.890 --> 00:45:27.150
I said stay. so you stayed?

495
00:45:27.230 --> 00:45:29.920
I can't even make a collie stay.

496
00:45:31.860 --> 00:45:34.660
I gotta check something.

497
00:45:34.730 --> 00:45:36.170
Stay.

498
00:45:43.140 --> 00:45:44.570
They're gone!

499
00:45:45.480 --> 00:45:47.540
They're all gone!

500
00:45:49.110 --> 00:45:51.950
- Do you know what today is?
- What?

501
00:45:53.280 --> 00:45:55.680
Today is tomorrow.

502
00:45:55.750 --> 00:45:57.450
It happened.

503
00:45:59.390 --> 00:46:01.590
- You're here.
- I'm here.

504
00:46:05.530 --> 00:46:10.130
Why weren't you like this last night?
You just fell sleep.

505
00:46:12.300 --> 00:46:14.790
It was the end
of a very long day.

506
00:46:18.180 --> 00:46:21.810
Is there anything
I can do for you today?.

507
00:46:21.880 --> 00:46:25.210
I'm sure I can think
of something.

508
00:46:58.620 --> 00:47:00.550
It's so beautiful!

509
00:47:11.200 --> 00:47:13.130
Let's live here.

510
00:47:23.310 --> 00:47:25.400
We'll rent to start.
